== read -t 0 polls, data ready reports success:
rc=0
== read -t 0 polls, EOF counts as readable:
rc=0
== read -t with data present returns it:
rc=0 x=[hello]
== read -t -n reads the count and stops:
rc=0 x=[abc]
== read -t times out on a silent producer, status is 142:
rc=142
== an unparsable timeout is rejected:
shit: 1:12: error: Builtin 'read': Invalid timeout specification.
     1 |  read -r -t nope x </dev/null; echo "rc=$?"
       |             ^~~~ here.
shit: note: The -t timeout needs a fractional second count such as 0.5.
rc=1
